<div class="note" topic="miscellaneous"><span class="heading centered smallCaps">Initial Report to <span link="https://liicornell.org/liifedent/congress" markup="no-show" occur="140" src="named_federal_agencies">Congress</span></span>
<p><a href="/rio/citation/Pub._L._99-433">Pub. L. 99–433, title IV, § 406(g)</a>, <span class="date" date="1986-10-01">Oct. 1, 1986</span>, <a href="/rio/citation/100_Stat._1034">100 Stat. 1034</a>, required that the first report submitted by the <span link="https://liicornell.org/liifedent/dod_osd_secretary_of_defense" occur="348" src="named_federal_agencies">Secretary of Defense</span> under subsec. (c) of this section after <span class="date" date="1986-10-01">Oct. 1, 1986</span>, would contain as much of the information required by former <a href="/uscode/text/10/667">section 667 of this title</a> as had been available to the Secretary at the time of its preparation.</p>
